folder: West Street & Desbrosses Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
West Street, Desbrosses to Watts Street. (Before Reconstruction).
President Borough of Manhattan.
June 9, 1918.

folder: West Street & Desbrosses Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1) West Street, east side, north from and including Desbrosses Street, to and including Watts Street. Also shown is Desbrosses Street, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of West Street.
March 6, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, showing a closer view of the S.E. corner of Watts Street.
September 27, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Desbrosses Street & West Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Desbrosses Street, north side, east from but not including West, to and including Greenwich Streets. The Desbrosses Street, Station of the Ninth Ave., Elevated is shown on Greenwich Street.

August 29, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: West Street & Desbrosses Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
West Street, west side, at the foot of Desbrosses Street, showing the Desbrosses Street Ferry and activity there. This photo is an enlargement from an original lantern slide.
